def: A vessel which receives the wort as it flows from the mashingtub.
An imitative word; an onomatopoetic word.

The seed of Strychnos Nuxvomica, a tree which abounds on theMalabar and Coromandel coasts of the East Indies. From this seed thedeadly poisons known as strychnine and brucine are obtained. Theseeds are sometimes called Quaker buttons.
The art or science of teaching.
The bleating of a sheep. Marryat.
A consort, husband or wife; a companion; a fere. [Obs.]
The act or process of nebulizing; atomization.
